  "local_port": 56634,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How Do I get Relaince Jio Sim?",
  "response": "Getting a Reliance Jio SIM is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Check Eligibility**\n- Ensure you have a valid government-issued ID proof (Aadhaar, PAN, Passport, etc.) and address proof.\n- Your mobile number should not be associated with more than 9 active SIMs across all operators in India (as per DoT regulations).\n\n---\n\n### **2. Visit a Reliance Jio Store or Retailer**\n- Locate the nearest Reliance Jio Store or authorized retailer. You can find one using the [Jio Store Locator](https://www.jio.com/store-locator) on their website.\n- Alternatively, you can visit a Reliance Digital store or any partner outlet selling Jio SIMs.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Provide KYC Details**\n- At the store or retailer, provide your KYC (Know Your Customer) documents, which include:\n  - **ID Proof**: Aadhaar, Passport, Voter ID, etc.\n  - **Address Proof**: Aadhaar, Utility Bill, etc.\n  - **Passport-sized photo** (in some cases).\n\n---\n\n### **4. Aadhaar Verification (if applicable)**\n- If using Aadhaar, you\u2019ll need to go through biometric authentication (fingerprint or iris scan) as part of the e-KYC process.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Choose Your Plan**\n- Select a prepaid or postpaid plan that suits your needs. The retailer will guide you through the available options.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Receive Your SIM**\n- After completing the formalities, you\u2019ll receive your Jio SIM card.\n- The SIM will usually be activated within a few hours or up to 24 hours.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Activate the SIM**\n- Insert the SIM into your phone.\n- Once activated, you\u2019ll receive a confirmation SMS from Jio.\n- Download the **MyJio app** to manage your account, recharge, and explore Jio services.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Online Option: Jio Website**\n- You can also order a Jio SIM online through the [Jio website](https://www.jio.com) or the MyJio app.\n- Fill in your details, provide KYC documents, and choose your plan.\n- A Jio executive will visit your address for KYC verification and deliver the SIM.\n\n---\n\n### **Required Documents**\n- **ID Proof**: Aadhaar, Passport, Voter ID, Driving License, etc.\n- **Address Proof**: Aadhaar, Passport, Utility Bill, etc.\n- **Passport-sized photograph** (if required).\n\n---\n\n### **Things to Keep in Mind**\n- Ensure your device is compatible with Jio\u2019s network (supports VoLTE).\n- The Jio SIM is free, but you\u2019ll need to recharge it with a plan to start using services.\n- If porting your number to Jio, carry your existing SIM and initiate the porting process.\n\nEnjoy seamless connectivity with Reliance Jio! \ud83d\ude0a",
